{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016B6w4btzRnGA5CGnedvWUJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks complete. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n**US-010 - BuildDataStruct kernel (cell start/end tables)**\n\n### Files created:\n- `fallingsand3d/physics/kernels/build_grid.cu` - K_BuildDataStruct CUDA kernel that detects cell boundaries in the sorted hash array and writes `cell_indexes_start[hash]` and `cell_indexes_end[hash]`\n- `fallingsand3d/build_grid.py` - Python wrapper: CuPy RawModule compilation, constant memory upload, array allocation (`allocate_cell_tables()`), kernel launch (`build_data_struct()`) with automatic memset of cell_start to 0xFFFFFFFF\n- `fallingsand3d/test_build_grid.py` - 8 integration tests all passing\n\n### Acceptance criteria verified:\n- cell_indexes_start[hash] = first particle index in cell\n- cell_indexes_end[hash] = one past last particle index  \n- Empty cells have cell_indexes_start = 0xFFFFFFFF\n- Arrays allocated as CuPy uint32 of size 125,000\n- Memset to 0xFFFFFFFF before each kernel launch\n- 8-particle/2-cell known config test passes\n- Sum of (cell_end - cell_start) across non-empty cells = num_particles\n- 500K particle stress test passes without errors\n- Block size = 256\n\n### Key difference from root-level prototype:\nThe fallingsand3d `common.cuh` already declares `__constant__ GridParams c_grid`, so `build_grid.cu` does NOT redeclare it (unlike the root prototype where each .cu file had its own `__constant__`).\n\n<promise>COMPLETE</promise>"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":85264,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":368},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3ee40f7f-a1c9-4640-b0e4-2236c98c5f30","uui